Compression

A perfect compression minimizes symbols while preserving semantic volume.

Compression ratio becomes

C=\frac{\text{Semantic Volume}}
{\text{Symbol Count}}

High-value communication has large V with few symbols.

That explains why:

* equations
* myths
* icons
* memes
* protocols

often outperform long explanations.

